726115f-a.text:
(1)
Atlantic Avenue, at 120th Street, showing the Long Island Railroad crossing a)d watch tower. The view is northeastward across the tracks on Atlantic Avenue, the frame houses being
on the thoroughfare's north side.
. L. Sperr  May 7, 1934
(e)
Viewing southeastward across the railroad crossing, the brick houses being on the east side of 120th Street.
P. L Sperr  May 7, 1934

725826f-a.text:
120th Street, east side, between Atlantic and 91st Avences, showing a frame house of odd architectural design. Note the balcony on the third floor, with the cupola-shaped roof.
P. L. Sperr  May 7, 1934
